      {
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How to calculate GST on MRP or inclusive price?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "<p>To calculate GST on an MRP price that includes GST, divide the total amount by (1 + GST rate/100) to get the net price, then subtract from the total amount to get GST. For example, if MRP is ₹1,180 with 18% GST, net price is ₹1,000 and GST is ₹180.</p>"
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the GST rate for restaurants and food services?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "<p>Restaurants and food services typically attract 5% GST without input tax credit or 18% GST with input tax credit, depending on the type of restaurant and services provided.</p>"
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How to calculate GST on services with multiple rates?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "<p>When multiple GST rates apply to different services, calculate GST for each service separately using the applicable rate and then sum up the total GST liability. Use our GST calculator with selectable rates for accurate computations.</p>"
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the difference between CGST, SGST, and IGST?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "<p>CGST is levied by the Central Government on intra-state supplies, SGST by the State Government on intra-state supplies, and IGST on inter-state supplies. For intra-state transactions, CGST and SGST are each half of the total GST rate. For inter-state transactions, IGST is the full GST rate.</p>"
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can I claim GST input tax credit on all purchases?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "<p>No, ITC cannot be claimed on certain supplies like food and beverages for personal consumption, outdoor catering, beauty treatment services, and goods used for personal consumption. Also, you can only claim ITC on business-related purchases with valid GST invoices.</p>"
            }
          }
        ]
      }
